Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Butter an 11-by-17- inch rimmed baking sheet; set aside. Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Stir in sugar and honey. Bring to a boil. Cook, without stirring, until mixture is medium amber and a candy thermometer registers 280 degrees;, about 6 minutes. Stir in pumpkin seeds. Cook until mixture reaches 300 degrees;, about 2 minutes. Pour onto prepared baking sheet. Let cool completely. Break into pieces.